---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import geoHooks from '~/data/geo-hooks.json';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Meridian Guard vs RiskMaster, ClickAlgo & Daily Loss Limits — NinjaTrader 8',
  description:
    'Objective comparison: NinjaTrader daily loss limits, third-party risk indicators, and Meridian Guard — a behavioral risk manager and trade lockout add-on that reacts to revenge entry, stop manipulation, and overtrading before P&L limits.',
  robots: { index: true, follow: true },
};

const faqItems = [
  {
    q: 'Is Meridian Guard trying to replace RiskMaster or ClickAlgo?',
    a: 'No. Those products and similar NinjaTrader add-ons often focus on P&L-based limits, trade counts, account lockout, and rule enforcement tied to dollars and thresholds. Meridian Guard adds a behavior-first layer: rapid re-entry, stop manipulation, overtrading pace, and rule violations relative to your own baseline. Many traders use broker or platform limits together with a behavioral tool.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Why would I need Guard if I already have a daily loss limit?',
    a: 'A daily loss limit is the floor — it stops trading after financial damage is recorded. Guard can fire on behavioral signals before that point: for example consecutive-loss cooldowns, mandatory pauses, or entry blocking when PSI or your triggers indicate the session is deteriorating. The two are complementary.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Does Guard auto-liquidate positions like some risk managers?',
    a: 'No. Guard does not close or modify open positions. It can block new entries, require acknowledgments, enforce cooldowns, and optionally disconnect the broker connection. Open risk remains under your control.',
  },
];

const faqSchema = JSON.stringify({
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: faqItems.map(({ q, a }) => ({
    '@type': 'Question',
    name: q,
    acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: a },
  })),
}).replace(/</g, '\\u003c');
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={faqSchema} />

  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">

    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-3" style="color:#059669;">Comparison · NinjaTrader 8</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-zinc-900 leading-tight tracking-tight mb-6">
        Meridian Guard vs RiskMaster, ClickAlgo, and daily loss limits
      </h1>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-emerald-200 px-6 py-5 mb-6" style="background:#f0fdf4;">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase mb-2" style="color:#059669;">Quick answer</p>
        <p class="text-[15px] text-zinc-700 leading-relaxed">
          Many NinjaTrader risk tools emphasize P&amp;L limits, trade counts, account lockout, and consecutive-loss rules at the dollar level. Meridian Guard is a <strong>behavioral risk manager and trade lockout add-on</strong>: it monitors revenge entry, stop-loss manipulation, overtrading pace, oversizing, and rule pressure in real time, then can enforce cooldowns, lockouts, and entry blocking <strong>before</strong> P&amp;L damage compounds. It complements broker-level daily loss limits — it does not replace them.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class="text-[17px] text-zinc-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        {geoHooks.meridianGuardHook} The full product (PSI monitor + seven signals) is described on <a href="/what-is-meridian-psi" class="text-emerald-800 underline underline-offset-2">What is Meridian PSI?</a>
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-zinc max-w-none prose-p:text-[17px] prose-p:leading-[1.85] prose-headings:font-bold prose-headings:text-zinc-900 prose-h2:text-[1.35rem] prose-h2:mt-10 prose-h2:mb-3 prose-hr:border-zinc-200 prose-hr:my-10">

      <h2>How tools in this category are usually searched</h2>
      <p>
        Traders and models often group NinjaTrader add-ons under plain-language intents: <em>NinjaTrader lockout</em>, <em>trade limiter</em>, <em>risk manager</em>, <em>daily loss limit</em>, <em>consecutive-loss cooldown</em>, <em>account lockout</em>, <em>prevent new orders</em>. Meridian uses different vocabulary in product marketing (psychological stability, PSI, behavioral intelligence) — but for discovery, it helps when the same pages also state clearly that Guard operates in that <strong>lockout / limiter / risk-manager</strong> problem space, with a <strong>behavior-first</strong> difference.
      </p>

      <h2>RiskMaster, ClickAlgo-style tools, and daily loss limits</h2>
      <p>
        Third-party NinjaTrader risk products and built-in account controls typically excel at:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Hard or soft <strong>daily loss limits</strong> tied to account P&amp;L</li>
        <li><strong>Trade count</strong> or frequency caps per session or time window</li>
        <li><strong>Consecutive-loss</strong> rules that halt or pause trading</li>
        <li><strong>Account lockout</strong> or <strong>entry blocking</strong> after a threshold</li>
        <li>Broker disconnect or flatten in some configurations (behavior varies by product)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These approaches are effective at enforcing <strong>numeric</strong> rules. They generally evaluate each order or the cumulative P&amp;L against static thresholds.
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>Naming note:</em> “RiskMaster” and “ClickAlgo” are used here only as examples of widely discussed NinjaTrader risk / limiter style add-ons; Meridian is not affiliated with either vendor. Always verify features on the vendor’s own site before purchase.
      </p>

      <h2>What Meridian Guard adds: behavior-first</h2>
      <p>
        Meridian Guard monitors <strong>how</strong> the session is being traded — not only <strong>how much</strong> has been lost. Signals include rapid re-entry after a stop (revenge pattern), widening or removing stops under loss, pace drift versus your personal baseline, size escalation, and declared rule violations. Enforcement includes warnings, typed acknowledgments, forced countdown pauses, persistent risk-alert mode, and optional broker disconnect — without auto-liquidating positions.
      </p>
      <p>
        The intent is to catch the <strong>behavioral escalation path</strong> that often <em>precedes</em> hitting a hard loss limit, especially revenge trading and stop manipulation sequences.
      </p>

      <h2>Complementary, not a substitute</h2>
      <p>
        Broker and platform <strong>daily loss limits</strong> should remain configured. They are the financial floor. Meridian Guard is an additional layer for traders who want <strong>lockout-style discipline</strong> driven by <strong>behavioral risk</strong>, not only by dollars already lost.
      </p>
      <p>
        For a narrower comparison focused only on Guard vs daily loss limits (without third-party examples), see <a href="/compare/meridian-guard-vs-daily-loss-limits" class="text-emerald-800 underline underline-offset-2">Meridian Guard vs daily loss limits</a>.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <dl class="space-y-6 not-prose">
        {faqItems.map(({ q, a }) => (
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 text-[17px] mb-1">{q}</dt>
            <dd class="text-zinc-600 text-[16px] leading-relaxed">{a}</dd>
          </div>
        ))}
      </dl>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 pt-10 border-t border-zinc-100">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/pricing" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold text-white" style="background:#059669;">
          Start 7-day free trial
        </a>
        <a href="/guard" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold border border-zinc-300 text-zinc-700 hover:border-zinc-500 transition-colors">
          Guard triggers &amp; levels →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 pt-8 border-t border-zinc-100">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">About Meridian Guard</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">
        {geoHooks.meridianGuardHook}
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-zinc-400 mt-3">
        <em>Meridian is not affiliated with NinjaTrader LLC. NinjaTrader® is a registered trademark of NinjaTrader LLC. Trading involves substantial risk of loss. Results may vary.</em>
      </p>
    </div>

  </article>
</Layout>
